 for bestpractices and # Cronjobs Dashboard

## Overview
Design and implement a cohesive, production-grade Cronjobs Dashboard within LifeOps that lists, filters, searches, enables/disables, bulk-manages cronjobs, offers a robust schedule builder, and provides a fast, accessible quick-create flow. The dashboard also interplays with a Cronjobs Engine (first-class cronjob objects with scheduling, triggers, constraints, safety rails, retry policy, and run recording), a full-featured Cronjob Editor, a Master Dashboard, and performance/optimization stacks (caching, indexing, monitoring). All UI must be responsive, accessible, and optimized for a developer/power-user audience.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
The Cronjobs Dashboard is a centralized page for discovering and managing cronjobs across LifeOps. It should:

- Display a searchable, filterable, and sortable table/list of cronjobs with the following columns:
  - Name
  - Enabled / Paused state
  - Schedule (human-readable + cron expression)
  - Next Run
  - Last Run Outcome (success, failure, skipped)
  - Target (agent or workflow)
  - Owner / Module
  - Tags / Labels
  - Actions (Quick Actions: Enable/Pause, Run Now, Edit, Clone, Delete)
- Provide a rich filter bar enabling:
  - Module (e.g., Content, Finance, Health, Developer)
  - Owner
  - Status (Enabled, Paused, All)
  - Tag/Label
  - Time window (for next run / last run)
- Support global search with autocomplete/dataset hints (e.g., by name, target, owner, tag)
- Include a Schedule Builder panel:
  - UI-based cron builder (with common presets: hourly, daily, weekly, monthly) and an option to switch to cron-expression input
  - Timezone selection with automatic UTC offset hints
  - Validation and live preview of next run times
- Provide Quick Create flow:
  - Minimal form that opens a Cronjob Editor modal or panel with essential fields pre-filled from templates
  - Validate inputs, provide inline guidance, and create a cronjob object in a single action
- Inline bulk actions:
  - Select multiple cronjobs and apply bulk enable/disable, delete, or run-now actions
  - Bulk editor support (optional): set a common schedule/target/constraints for a selection
- Cronjob Editor page:
  - Full CRUD editor for cronjob objects
  - Fields: name, schedule (UI builder or cron expression), timezone, trigger type, target (agent/workflow), input payload template, permissions & automation level, constraints, safety rails, retry policy, outputs configuration
